  "prompt": "My father coming from kanpur on nanded got 6:30 hr late and now no where to go as he has to come to bti on punjab mail. Who is responsible for that?",
  "response": "Train delays can be caused by a variety of factors such as weather conditions, technical issues, track maintenance, or operational challenges. Responsibility can vary depending on the specific cause of the delay. Generally, the railway authority or company operating the train is responsible for managing and addressing these delays. However, it's also important to note that some delays may be beyond their control.\n\nIn this situation, it might be helpful to contact the railway's customer service for assistance or clarification on the delay and to ensure your father can board the next available train to Bathinda (BTI). They may also provide guidance or options for rerouting or compensation if applicable.",
